<title>Untitled document</title>
<br />
<p>The biggest issues facing students are often only visible to the students themselves. For that reason, the Student Representative Council is interested in your <em>Bright Ideas </em>to improve the student experience at BYU-Idaho.</p>
<p>As you submit your <em>Bright Idea</em>s ensure that they are:</p>
<p><strong>Global</strong>- The SRC is most able to help with problems and solutions that affect a large number of students. If you have an individual issue/complaint we encourage you to contact <a href="x37128.xml">Ask BYU-Idaho</a>, which can connect you directly to the person best able to resolve your individual problem.</p>
<p><strong>Appropriate</strong> - Is your solution compatible with the objectives of the SRC and the <a href="x9274.xml">BYU-Idaho mission statement</a>?</p>
<p><strong>Practical </strong>- Some issues that may keep a resolution from being practical are financial and legal concerns.</p>
<p>Now, tell us your idea!</p>
